- The integer result is the largest variance possible among all substrings of the input string `s`.
- The input string `s` consists of lowercase English letters only.
- The length of the input string `s` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 10000.
- The variance of a string is defined as the largest difference between the number of occurrences of any 2 characters present in the string.
- The variance of a substring is a contiguous sequence of characters within a string.